      • getValue

        public E getValue()

        getValue.

        Return the last value in the list when only one is expected. And this method is for when only one value is expected. It is possible for the user to re-specify the same command on the input. That would build an array as if it were a multi-value argument. But since it is not, we return the last one specified.
        Specified by:
        getValue in interface ICmdLineArg<E>
        Returns:
        a E object.
